OBJECTIVE: Shortened life expectancy of people with mental disorders has been 
attributed to medical comorbidities, yet these conditions remain 
under-recognized and under-treated. This study characterizes the medical demands 
placed on inpatient psychiatric units to help guide medical assessment and 
